  "tldr": [
    {
      "source": "hackernews",
      "subsource": "news.ycombinator.com",
      "category": "ai",
      "title": "OpenAI and Hugging Face address security incident during model evaluation",
      "url": "https://openai.com/index/hugging-face-model-evaluation-security-incident/",
      "discuss_url": "https://news.ycombinator.com/item?id=48997548",
      "score": 1374,
      "comments": 926,
      "author": "mfiguiere",
      "published": "2026-07-21T20:09:52Z",
      "bullets": [
        "OpenAI and Hugging Face mitigated a July 2026 security incident involving automated model evaluation and benchmarking workflows.",
        "Unsafe code execution from untrusted model weights or scripts poses severe remote code execution risks to evaluation infrastructure.",
        "AI security teams must strictly sandbox dynamic evaluation pipelines, enforcing zero-trust egress controls and isolated container runtimes."
      ]
    },
    {
      "source": "lobsters",
      "subsource": "lobste.rs/programming",
      "category": "engineering",
      "title": "libei integrations in the XDG RemoteDesktop and InputCapture portals",
      "url": "http://who-t.blogspot.com/2026/07/libei-integrations-in-xdg-remotedesktop.html",
      "discuss_url": "https://lobste.rs/s/egdij3",
      "score": 3,
      "comments": 0,
      "author": "calvin",
      "published": "2026-07-22T07:21:31Z",
      "bullets": [
        "libei standardizes sandboxed input emulation on Wayland, replacing legacy X11 XTest mechanisms with secure client-receiver D-Bus communication channels.",
        "xdg-desktop-portal RemoteDesktop integration uses libei to securely inject synthetic mouse and keyboard events into sandboxed Wayland sessions.",
        "The InputCapture portal leverages libei to safely intercept and forward local hardware events to external devices across desktop boundary edges."
      ]
    },
    {
      "source": "lobsters",
      "subsource": "lobste.rs/security",
      "category": "security",
      "title": "LG to Ban Residential Proxies from Smart TV Apps",
      "url": "https://krebsonsecurity.com/2026/07/lg-to-ban-residential-proxies-from-smart-tv-apps/",
      "discuss_url": "https://lobste.rs/s/ny0yzm",
      "score": 40,
      "comments": 6,
      "author": "raymii",
      "published": "2026-07-22T05:56:08Z",
      "bullets": [
        "Monetization SDKs embedded in webOS apps frequently turn smart TVs into unauthorized residential proxy nodes for third-party traffic.",
        "Cybercriminals exploit these residential IPs to bypass WAFs, rate limits, and anti-bot defenses in automated credential stuffing attacks.",
        "Banning proxyware targets IoT device abuse, preventing consumer hardware from being weaponized within commercial proxy networks."
      ]
    },
    {
      "source": "lobsters",
      "subsource": "lobste.rs/devops",
      "category": "devops",
      "title": "GitHub suddenly rejected my SSH key (the fix was a .pub file?!)",
      "url": "https://thorsell.io/2026/07/21/github-ssh-keys.html",
      "discuss_url": "https://lobste.rs/s/twqtlo",
      "score": 56,
      "comments": 18,
      "author": "GLaDER",
      "published": "2026-07-21T10:11:59Z",
      "bullets": [
        "OpenSSH clients require local .pub files alongside private keys to correctly offer public key parameters and negotiate signature algorithms with GitHub.",
        "Missing public key files cause silent SSH authentication failures in automated pipelines, CI/CD runners, and developer environments.",
        "Store corresponding .pub files alongside private keys or explicitly map IdentityFile paths in local and CI SSH configurations."
      ]
    },
